                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39) City of Flint/42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-27T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 27, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 27—6:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>810. My 809, October 27, 5 a.m. I was unable to obtain the promised telephone
                    communication with the Captain or a member of the crew of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >City of Flint</hi> at 8 this morning, although temporary communication with
                    the Murmansk operator was established. As calls for Murmansk are only accepted
                    for certain hours during the day the next attempt will be made at 1:30
                    today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
